      "metadata": {
        "source": "github.readme"
      },
      "html": "\n<blockquote>\n<p>npm install -g dat-share-all</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Share all dats that are below a directory. Useful if developing with multiple dats.</p>\n<p>The official <a href=\"https://github.com/dat/dat\">dat-cli</a> shares a single dat (by default the path from where called). With <code>dat-share-all</code> you share all dats that are located below a directory.</p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>npm install -g dat-share-all</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<p>From a folder that has dats below it:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>dat-share-all</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Options:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>--watch</code>: Watch for new dats being created and automatically share them too (default: false)</li>\n<li><code>--import</code>: Watch for file changes and import and share them (default: false)</li>\n<li><code>--dir</code>: Set basedir from where to look for dats (default: current dir)</li>\n<li><code>--curses</code>: Use a curses-style UI (based on <a href=\"https://github.com/chjj/blessed\">blessed</a>)</li>\n</ul>\n"
